<http://www.oie.int/Messages/040617PER.htm>

Foot and mouth disease (FMD) in Peru
-------------------------------------
(Date of previous outbreak of FMD in Peru reported to the OIE: October 2000).
Information received on 17 Jun 2004 from Dr Oscar Dominguez Falcon,
Director General for Animal Health, National Animal Health Service,
Ministry of Agriculture, Lima:
Date of the report: 17 Jun 2004.
FMD due to virus serotype O was reported in 8 fattening cattle, in 3 farms
in Lurin district, Lima Department, in a zone where vaccination is
practised and where no cases of the disease had been detected since October
2000. Laboratory diagnosis was made on 11 and 14 Jun 2004.
Sanitary measures taken:
- Destruction of all 8 positive cattle.
- Slaughter of all 80 contact cattle.
- Vaccination and booster vaccination in the area.
- Movement restrictions for susceptible species into and out of the
affected area.
- Upholding and strengthening of epidemiological surveillance by
serological monitoring.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[During 2003, FMD was officially reported from 3 South American countries:
Argentina, Bolivia, and Paraguay. - Mod.AS]
